  "prompt": "Where do I download Quora for Windows 10?",
  "response": "As of my last update, there is no official Quora app specifically for Windows 10. However, you can access Quora through any web browser on your Windows 10 device by visiting the website at [www.quora.com](https://www.quora.com).\n\nIf you prefer a more app-like experience, you can create a shortcut to the Quora website on your desktop for easier access. Here\u2019s how:\n\n1. Open your web browser and go to [www.quora.com](https://www.quora.com).\n2. Click on the three dots (or the equivalent menu) in the upper right corner of the browser.\n3. Look for an option like \"More tools\" or \"Add to desktop\" (the wording may vary depending on the browser).\n4. Choose to create a shortcut.\n\nThis will allow you to open Quora directly from your desktop like an application. \n\nAlternatively, you could check the Microsoft Store to see if any third-party apps exist that provide Quora access, but be cautious with third-party applications regarding privacy and security.",
